{"id":570927,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tzvetan_Todorov","text":"Tzvetan Todorov (;; March 1, 1939 \u2013 February 7, 2017) was a Bulgarian-French historian, philosopher, structuralist literary critic, sociologist and essayist.\nHe was the author of many books and essays, which have had a significant influence in anthropology, sociology, semiotics, literary theory, thought history and culture theory.\nTodorov died on February 7, 2017 in Paris, aged 77.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Bulgarians","surface_form":"Bulgarian","offset":60},{"uri":"France","surface_form":"French","offset":70},{"uri":"Historian","surface_form":"historian","offset":77},{"uri":"Philosopher","surface_form":"philosopher","offset":88},{"uri":"Structuralism","surface_form":"structuralist","offset":101},{"uri":"Literary_critic","surface_form":"literary critic","offset":115},{"uri":"Sociologist","surface_form":"sociologist","offset":132},{"uri":"Anthropology","surface_form":"anthropology","offset":244},{"uri":"Sociology","surface_form":"sociology","offset":258},{"uri":"Semiotics","surface_form":"semiotics","offset":269},{"uri":"Literary_theory","surface_form":"literary theory","offset":280},{"uri":"History_of_ideas","surface_form":"thought history","offset":297},{"uri":"Culture_theory","surface_form":"culture theory","offset":317},{"uri":"Paris","surface_form":"Paris","offset":369}]}